DIV1.P:
What do you mean, says I, I think I swore at him;
what do ye sneer at now? you have always one dry Rub or
another to give us.

Nay, says William, thou art in the right there;
we must never talk of repenting while we con∣tinue
Pirates.

Here we converted all our Effects into Money,
settled our Abode as for a considerable Time, and
William and I maintaining an inviolable Friendship
and Fidelity to one another, lived like two Bro∣thers;
we neither had or sought any separate In∣terest;
we convers'd seriously and gravely, and
upon the Subject of our Repentance continually;
we never changed, that is to say, so as to leave
off our Armenian Garbs, and we were called at Ve∣nice
the two Grecians.
